---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Portfolio | About" description="How this portfolio is built: stack, architecture, and chatbot limits.">
  <section>
    <span class="brand-pill">About</span>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-bold text-ink sm:text-4xl">About This Portfolio</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8 grid gap-5 lg:grid-cols-2">
    <article class="card-surface p-7">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink">Core Technologies</h2>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-ink/80">
        <li><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Astro + TypeScript:</span> fast, static-first rendering with type safety.</li>
        <li><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Tailwind CSS:</span> utility-driven styling for consistent design tokens.</li>
        <li><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Vercel Function API route:</span> lightweight backend endpoint for chat requests.</li>
        <li><span class="font-semibold text-ink">LLM inference:</span> TogetherAI with gpt-oss-120b.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card-surface p-7">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink">Data And Rendering Model</h2>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-ink/80">
        <li><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Context-driven data:</span> profile, achievements, and certifications are loaded from local context files.</li>
        <li><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Static-first pages:</span> most content is pre-rendered for speed and SEO.</li>
        <li><span class="font-semibold text-ink">Interactive island:</span> chat UI hydrates only where interactivity is needed.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 card-surface p-7 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink">Chatbot Limits And Safety</h2>
    <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 leading-7 text-ink/80">
      <p>
        The assistant is useful for exploration and first drafts, but it can still generate incorrect,
        outdated, or incomplete answers. Important decisions should always be verified with reliable
        documentation and human review.
      </p>
      <p>
        Responses depend on model behavior and prompt context. This means output quality can vary,
        and some nuanced personal or project-specific details may be missed.
      </p>
      <p>
        <span class="text-moss">Rate limiting (5 questions per session)</span> and lightweight protections are applied to keep the service available and reduce
        abuse, but availability may still be impacted by provider-side constraints.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 card-surface p-7 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-ink">Deployment And Operations</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 leading-7 text-ink/80">
      The project deploys on Vercel with GitHub Actions workflows: one for tests and one for
      production deployment after main-branch tests succeed. This keeps delivery predictable while
      preserving fast iteration.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
